Learning Outcomes
  What is the basic list syntax?
    <ul> or <ol>
      <li>
    </ul> or </ol>

  How do you nest lists inside each other?
    <ul>
      <li>...</li>
      <li>
        <ol>
          <li>...</li>
        </ol>
      </li>
    </ul>


Unordered List CSS Property
  list-style-type property
    disc
      = bullet points
    circle
      = circle
    square
      = square
    none
      = unmarked
    decimal, decimal-leading-zero, lower-roman, upper-roman, lower-greek, lower-alpha / lower-latin
    upper-alpha / upper-latin, armenian, georgian

  Adding Image as List Style
    list-style-type: none;
    background: url("custom-icon.png") 0 50% no-repeat;
    padding-left: 12px

Ordered List HTML Attribute
  type
    1
      = numbered with numbers
    A
      = numbered with uppercase letters
    a
      = numbered with lowercase letters
    I
      = numbered with uppercase roman numerals
    i
      = numbered with lowercase roman numerals

  start
    determines the starting number, only accepts integer value

  reversed
    list appears in reverse order
    is boolean

  value
    change its value within the list
    all subsequent items follow that value

Description List
  <dl>
    <dt>Term</dt>
    <dd>description of term</dd>
  </dl>

  can contain numerous terms and descriptions
  can have multiple terms per description
  and multiple descriptions per term


Display Horizontally
  CSS
    float: left;
      OR
    display: inline;
      OR
    display: inline-block; (most common because you can add spacing and vertical margins)

    note: when changing display, the list item marker is removed
          this does not occur when floating, however we most always clear our floats

CSS List Style Position
  list-style-position
    outside (default)
      content appear directly to the right, outside of list item marker
      no content can wrap below it
    inside (rare)
      places list item marker in line with the first line of the <li> element
    inherit

CSS Shorthand
  list-style
    combines list-style-type and list-style-position
    first list list-style type, then list-style-position
    example:
      list-style: circle inside;


Lists
  Three Types
    1) Unordered
    2) Ordered
    3) Description
